        "body": "<p>See this question: <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/3581816/i-need-a-simple-java-example-of-processing-a-json-response-via-http-for-android\">I need a simple java example of processing a JSON response via HTTP for Android App?<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>There seems to be nothing special with openexchangerates. Just get the JSON data with HTTP GET and create an object out of it. You can create a class for the exchange rate and use <a href=\"https://sites.google.com/site/gson/gson-user-guide\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">GSON<\/a> to instantiate the object.<\/p>\n",
